snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 6/25 - 6/29
snippet.description: We're back from VidCon! And special guest TomSka joins us this week as we do a bit of beatboxing, argue over when pornography was invented, and discover a universal truth: Girls don't give a shit about "The Simpsons," even when it was good.

snippet.title: The Ultimate Cheat
snippet.description: Epic poems, Mesopotamian myths, and tales as old as time all have one thing in common: great warriors and their search for the truth of the universe, the key to unlocking ultimate power. Some call that key God; others, Yahweh; still others, the elusive trickster demon known as Ko-na-mi.

snippet.title: That Time of The Month
snippet.description: Ever since the company switched their target demo to "Stupid men who couldn't possibly understand what we go through every month," sales have increased 36,000%.

snippet.title: 5sf's VidCon Panel
snippet.description: Special thanks to the organizers, YouTubers, volunteers, and of course, all the fans for hating the living hell out of us! We love you unconditionally, no matter how many times you punch us in the face or pull our pants down during a panel!

snippet.title: Rich Man, Poor Man
snippet.description: Well, that's the last time Michel Rousselette III buys a golden trash bin portal off of SkyMall. What's the point if all you're going to attract are the riff-raff?

snippet.title: Throwing It Out There
snippet.description: Nobody likes a long-winded, regretful tirade about an ex-wife, not even inanimate objects. Watch how mere physics can cut a philosophical discussion short in seconds flat.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 6/18 - 6/22
snippet.description: INVESTIGATIVE. REPORTING. I get the in-depth analysis from real people on real comments, in a real park. This is some serious man-on-the-street ish.

snippet.title: Etiquette Class
snippet.description: However, it is customary to take the 30 milligrams of 2C-B from the dealer on your left (and ONLY your left), so on that front he did quite well, even if he did it 20 minutes before class started.

snippet.title: An American In London
snippet.description: At last, a Tea Party for people who actually drink tea.

snippet.title: Prank Call
snippet.description: Scouts would always come calling, in the rare, impossible off-chance that he'd lace up once more. They knew, even if he came back, that nothing would ever be the same again after the leftover curry incident in the '84 games. Like the refrigerator himself, they just wanted another chance to believe.

snippet.title: Isolation Hills
snippet.description: Offers twice the seclusion of Away-From-It-All Falls, and even more of that eerie feeling that you may be alone in the universe than Forest Glen, Maryland!

snippet.title: Brain Transplant
snippet.description: To be fair, a girl being bad at giving handjobs is like a man being bad at pairing off a cute skirt with chunky shoes. If you're actually good at it, it says something about you that you might not want to be said.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 6/11 - 6/15
snippet.description: Epic staredowns, cold-blooded disses, constant masturbation jokes, timeouts and boobs: This week is like preschool all over again!

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #190
snippet.description: A crappy anniversary gift given to an Amnesiac Bridge Troll echoes bad memories of the lost friendship he had with the Devil and his father.

snippet.title: Dad Therapy
snippet.description: Some therapists' schedules are just too full to have individual sessions with the kids and the dads. For those people, there's another option. Bring your coupon in on Father's Day and get a free shirt.

snippet.title: Dealing With The Devil
snippet.description: When the devil asks you to name your price, think long and hard. Don't you have enough friends in your social circle? Do you really need another check to pick up at restaurants, another midnight ticket to score for The Dark Knight Rises?

snippet.title: Echo (Echo)
snippet.description: He didn't mean to say he loved you, it just came out that way. (Sure it did.) No, really, he's pretty beaten-up about it and wants to just start over from scratch. (I don't really care, I'm a canyon, I have other things to do.) Can you at least give him a chance? (How many ways can I echo 'No'?)

snippet.title: Amnesiac Bridge Troll
snippet.description: The real bitch of it is, you have to give each of those three questions a different answer, and if he doesn't believe you on all of them, you're getting eaten. The smart ones say "Under a Bridge, Silver Spring, and North America," and they make it out with just a limb missing or something.

snippet.title: Mini Anniversary
snippet.description: Luckily you can't go to jail for vehicular manslaughter when you're not in the car, so one trip to the undertaker and a coat of Turtle Wax later, everything was good as new with no one the wiser.

snippet.title: 5sf Fans Read: "And Still I Search" by Brian Firenzi
snippet.description:
Last week (http://youtu.be/g2H9xjMMlTE) we asked our followers on YouTube to find an essay from "Chicken Soup for the Teenage Soul" that Brian wrote when he was 15. The first person to e-mail us with a video of them reading it aloud will receive a prize (in this case, BuddhaBot), but here's a montage of every video we received anyway.

We apologize for any suffering we may have caused by spreading awareness of Brian's essay.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #189
snippet.description: A foul ball strikes a man in the head worsening his mental illness of drinking 40's and arm wrestling the angel of death just to get some useless facts about cooking.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 6/4 - 6/8
snippet.description: We were all quite hungry this week, so while it may seem a little rushed, this video still gets you: a 2-year-old movie reference, an impromptu singalong, special-guest-star-who-is-always-here Michael Rousselet, and a rousing call to live life to the fullest. Speaking of full, what's the number of that Mexican place that does the incredible chorizo burrito?

snippet.title: Useless Fact Cowboy: Kitchen Edition
snippet.description: He was falling on hard times. He even started resorting to useful facts, like how many calories are in a bucket of chicken wings, or how a bill becomes a law. Sadly, no one saw this as the cry for help that it was.

snippet.title: Game of Death
snippet.description: He also would've settled for a round of Twister, seeing as how either game allows his sickly touch of death to course through your body and eliminate you instantly. Plus, the lack of joints makes him insanely flexible.

snippet.title: Edward 40 Hands
snippet.description: The haunting, goth-lite romantic tale of a girl who felt like an outcast in her own world, and a bro who took the whole "frat game" thing way too far.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #188
snippet.description: An airplane crashes on a stylish island but the survivors' illiteracy doesn't allow them to succeed in the creative world, so they have to interview bands in order to pass the time until their bank accounts deplete.

snippet.title: A 5sf Challenge
snippet.description: And what's worse, they even air-mailed DVDs to our grieving families, with hi-def footage of us unknowingly masturbating in front of our hacked webcams. You gotta hand it to hackers: They're thorough.

snippet.title: Grouplove at the Gorge
snippet.description: Rouss had a chance to at least get one more question out of the guitarist before he hit the ground, like "What would your last words be if you died today, since you certainly are going to?" Alas, there wasn't really a way to hear his hypothetical response, and Rousselet just isn't that quick on his feet.

snippet.title: Hitting The Books
snippet.description: He loses the big fight against Infinite Jest (spoilers!) but in the end, his big heart still inspired the nation by going the distance: All 1079 pages, without understanding a single word of any of it.

snippet.title: New Style
snippet.description: Seriously, Jon. The pirate look is so last--(goes to wikipedia, searches "When Was Pirates?" returns no results, wait oh shit, am I writing this research process down as I do it? Why can't I stop or delete any of this? Oh well, one more shitty description in a sea of terrible, atrocious prose)

snippet.title: Week #187 In Review
snippet.description: A grammatically challenged and power-hungry film director weared a tuxedo on stage, causing his roommate to immediately quit the band and and become a struggling VJ for concerts and music festivals.

snippet.title: P.A. Interview
snippet.description: "5sf's Rock Talk" was abruptly cancelled after network execs deemed the content to be too hip and edgy. They then hired a new group of hip, edgy internet comedians for a 4-year, $2,000 contract, then went home to the kitchen and made sweet love to their wives on the new marble countertops.

snippet.title: My Roommate Quit The Band
snippet.description: It went on like this for measures and measures, until one day, something about Paul's snotty, bossy pre-chorus just made Alec snap and get the knife...and then clean it with soapy water. Hey-o! Betcha thought that was gonna be about murder, huh? Nope! Alec just committed suicide right after, that's all.

snippet.description: By the time the air raid sirens reverberated through the unsuspecting suburbs, it was already too late. Experiment #54-AMPM, codename "Too Much Good Stuff," had gone rogue somewhere in the northern region of Silver Spring.

Also, fucking kill me now.
